# Commit Messages

We follow a structured commit format inspired by [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).
This helps keep the commit history readable and ensures consistent release versioning.

## Format

<type>(<optional scope>): <short summary>

[optional body]

## Breaking Changes

For breaking changes, append `!` after the type/scope:

<type>(<optional scope>)!: <short summary>

Or include a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer in the commit body.

## Allowed Commit Types

| Type     | Description                                          |
| -------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| feat     | A new feature or enhancement                         |
| fix      | A bug fix                                            |
| refactor | Code refactoring that doesn't change behavior        |
| docs     | Documentation-only changes                           |
| chore    | Maintenance tasks (e.g. CI, packaging, dependencies) |
| style    | Code style or formatting changes (no logic impact)   |
| perf     | Performance improvements                             |
| ci       | CI/CD pipeline changes                               |

## Common Scopes

| Scope      | Example                                          | Description                |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------- |
| components | `feat(components): add Card component`           | React components           |
| tokens     | `fix(tokens): export missing color variable`     | Design tokens              |
| brand      | `chore(brand): add grow-the-music-tree mark`     | Static brand artwork (`src/brand/`) |
| favicons   | `feat(favicons): add gtmt favicon bundle`        | Favicon bundles            |
| styles     | `fix(styles): correct reset specificity`         | Global styles/CSS          |
| hooks      | `feat(hooks): add useMediaQuery hook`            | Shared React hooks         |
| utils      | `refactor(utils): simplify color helpers`        | Helpers and constants      |
| deps       | `chore(deps): update tsup to v9`                 | Dependency management      |

## Examples

feat(components): add Card component with outlined variant
fix(tokens): export missing surface color token
chore(brand): add grow-the-music-tree mark assets
docs: update contributing guide
chore(deps): update tsup to v9
ci: add publish workflow for GitHub Packages
feat(components)!: rename Button size prop values

BREAKING CHANGE: Button size prop now uses "sm", "md", "lg" instead of "small", "medium", "large".

## Guidelines

Use imperative mood ("add", "fix", not "added", "fixed").

Keep the summary under 72 characters.

Use the commit body for additional context if needed.

One logical change per commit.

Small, focused commits are better than large, mixed ones.
